  "prompt": "What universities does Federal Signal recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Federal Signal Corporation, a company that specializes in environmental and safety solutions, recruits new graduates from various universities across the United States. While the specific universities may vary from year to year depending on their recruitment needs, they typically target schools with strong engineering and business programs. Some of the universities Federal Signal may recruit from include:\n\n1. University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign\n2. Purdue University\n3. Illinois Institute of Technology\n4. Northwestern University\n5. University of Michigan\n6. Georgia Institute of Technology\n7. Texas A&M University\n8. University of Wisconsin-Madison\n\nAs for the majors Federal Signal looks for in new graduates, they typically seek candidates with degrees in the following fields:\n\n1. Mechanical Engineering\n2. Electrical Engineering\n3. Industrial Engineering\n4. Computer Science\n5. Software Engineering\n6. Business Administration\n7. Finance\n8. Accounting\n9. Marketing\n10. Supply Chain Management\n\nKeep in mind that Federal Signal's specific recruitment needs may change from year to year, and they may target additional universities or majors based on their current business requirements. It's always a good idea for interested students to check Federal Signal's career website or attend career fairs to learn more about their current recruitment focus and opportunities for new graduates.",
